Method Detail

getOffset

public int getOffset()
Description copied from interface: ISenseEntry
The synset offset is the byte offset that the synset containing the sense is found at in the database "data" file corresponding to the part of speech encoded in the sense key. A synset offset if an integer in the closed range [0, 99999999], and is encoded in the sense file as an 8 digit, zero-filled decimal integer.

Specified by:
getOffset in interface ISenseEntry

getSenseKey

public ISenseKey getSenseKey()
Description copied from interface: ISenseEntry
A sense key is an encoding of the word sense. Programs can construct a sense key in this format and use it as a binary search key into the sense index file.

Specified by:
getSenseKey in interface ISenseEntry

getTagCount

public int getTagCount()
Description copied from interface: ISenseEntry
The tag count represents the number of times the sense is tagged in various semantic concordance texts. A count of 0 indicates that the sense has not been semantically tagged.
